        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">W=4, A=1, L=1, T=1, Z=10 · 5 letters · Z+W combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The elegant ballroom dance in triple time. WALTZ is a Z-word masterpiece — 17 points from just 5 tiles (3.4 per tile). It uses the Z with W, clearing two awkward consonants in one play. Plus it hooks to WALTZED (19pts) and WALTZES (18pts).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💃 JIVE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · J=8, I=1, V=4, E=1 · Swing dance</p></div>
